The subject provides an overview of creative entrepreneurship, its future trends and theories. In the course, the development of an idea into a business model is practically carried out in teams, and a business plan is drawn up and presented.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The purpose of the subject is to provide participants with theoretical knowledge of the specifics and business opportunities of the field of creative entrepreneurship, as well as a methodological framework and practical teamwork experience for developing the chosen idea into a business model, analyzing the business model, checking the main business hypotheses, and preparing and presenting a business plan.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student: *understands the specifics of creative business and the most important trends; *can analyze the most important social, cultural and economic trends and the resulting business opportunities in the creative industry; *selects a strategically suitable business idea for development; *understands the nature of the brand and knows how to methodically apply the acquired knowledge in brand development; *can design a budget and manage it; *applies business hypothesis validation methodology in product or service development; * prepares a business plan and presents it both in writing and orally; *applies the principles of sustainable development when developing a business plan.
